news.title: Mumbai: BMC panel clears part of Rs 574 crore project for redevelopment
news.para: The committee cleared proposals for redevelopment of conservancy workers’ quarters in N ward (Chirag Nagar), L (Lions Garden), S (Amrapali Building) and T wards (Gaikwad Nagar). Proposals for redeveloping quarters in P-South (Mithanagar, Pragati Nagar) were also cleared. This project will cost BMC Rs 351 crore.

news.title: Plea lodged with UP vigilance department for FIR against accused in Supertech case
news.para: NOIDA CEO Ritu Maheshwari confirmed the development and said the authority will be going ahead with demolition planning of the twin towers that have come up in Sector 93A of the city in violation of building norms.

news.title: Sebi tweaks norms for REITs, InvITs on exit option for dissenting unit holders
news.para: The exit option for dissenting unit holders would be available in case of an acquisition, change in sponsor, inducted sponsor or change in control of sponsor or inducted sponsor is triggered pursuant to an open offer.

news.title: Arihant Superstructures to raise up to Rs 500 core through securities
news.para: The issue of securities could be through private placement, preferential issue, qualified institutions placement (QIP), follow-on public offering ("FPO"), or a combination thereof.

news.title: Noida authority to survey all green belts' projects after Supertech twin towers fiasco
news.para: The Noida Authority will take a look at all green belts within group housing societies and around commercial complexes. The city’s earmarked green belt area is 800 acres. Officials will survey green belts that are within complexes soon.

news.title: Unitech's promoter diverted Rs 2,345 crore to foreign countries: ED
news.para: The ED said that during the course of the investigation, it was revealed that the promoters of Unitech Group in collusion with their associates generated proceeds of crime to the tune of Rs 7,638.43 Crore.

news.title: Great Portland sells London office building for $247 million
news.para: The London-focused firm said its joint venture with BP Pension Fund - Great Ropemaker Partnership - sold 160 Old Street, which sits at the heart of the Silicon Roundabout business district, to a fund advised by J.P. Morgan Global Alternatives at a 5% premium to its March valuation.

news.title: Fitch slashes Chinese home builder Fantasia's rating on bond worries
news.para: Fitch's cut Fantasia's rating to 'CCC-' from 'B', also warning that uncertainty over its finances meant there was a "significant" risk it would not make a $208 million payment due on one of its higher-profile international bonds on Monday.

news.title: China property sector default woes deepen amid Evergrande disquiet
news.para: Evergrande is facing one of the country's largest-ever debt restructurings as it wrestles with more than $300 billion of debt. The company last month missed making coupon payments on two dollar bond tranches.

news.title: Chinese developer Fantasia fails to make debt payments
news.para: Fears of contagion through the Chinese economy have grown as Evergrande, the most indebted of the country's private homebuilders, struggles with more than $300 billion in liabilities and heads towards a massive restructuring.

news.title: Builder-buyers meetings planned to resolve dispute in Greater Noida
news.para: The meeting related to Greenshire project located in Sector 2 of Nirala Projects is scheduled on October 7, Paramount Emotions at Sector 1 of Paramount Pro Build on October 8, Radha Sky Garden at Sector 16B, SJP Infratech on October 11, Kasawood Stock at Sector-16C, Angel InfraHeight on October 18 and Radhe Krishna Technobuild Sector-16 on October 21.

news.title: Gurugram: Gates can no longer be installed at will inside colonies
news.para: Town planner RS Batth said according to the Haryana Development and Regulation of Urban Areas Act, 1975, any gate put up on 24-metre-wide roads, sector-dividing roads or any public road is illegal.

news.title: HC to hear case of illegal buildings near Goa international airport
news.para: During the hearing, the Chicalim panchayat will also submit an affidavit regarding the 74 structures that have come up within the funnel zone without any permission from the Mormugao planning and development authority (MPDA).

news.title: Jaipur: Land record maps in shambles, all documents to go digital
news.para: JMC-Heritage commissioner Avadhesh Meena said, “We will digitise all land record maps. After the process is complete, people can access the photocopies while the originals will be kept securely to prevent further decay of paper.”

news.title: Prime minister hands over keys to 75,000 PMAY beneficiaries in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: Narendra Modi digitally handed over keys of PMAY-U houses to the beneficiaries and interacted with them.
